						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Airāvatēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājādhirāja II: Year lost.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Kaḍalśūḻnda-pārmādarum,</hi> etc., of the king who ascended the throne in c. 1166 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a copy of the order of the king <hi rend="italic">(tirumugappaḍi)</hi> and refers to the king Tribhuvanachchakkaravartti Kō[nēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ*]. The details of the record are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
